Five people have been Killed and two seriously injured when taxi and a car collided at James van Huyssteen Drive in Bethlehem on Tuesday.Reports from the scene indicate that a taxi and a Toyota Corolla collided head-on.Netcare 911 said, &#8220;Paramedics arrived at the scene and found the wreckages of both vehicles in the veldt next to the roadway with some of the injured still trapped in the twisted metal.&#8220;After the injured were triaged it was found that five occupants from the Toyota tragically died and two from the taxi are in a serious condition.&#8221;All patients were stabilised on the scene and then transported to Dihlabeng Hospital.Exact details to the cause of the crash and preceding events will form part of the police investigation.TNA Reporter